{
  "texts": [
    "To in- fuse discourse structure into LoRA, we begin by converting RST structures, generated by an RST parser 2 into a compact matrix representation.",
    "Figure 2 exemplifies how to transmute the full potential RST structures (n-best RST forests) into a three-dimensional discourse matrix (Pu et al., 2023).",
    "In this matrix, the x and y axes correspond to the elementary discourse units (EDUs) within the source document, while the z-axis denotes the discourse relation label 3.",
    "Each point of the matrix indicates the probability value p(edu i, edu j, r k) ∈ [0, 1] ⊆ R that edu i is the nucleus of edu j with discourse relation r k.",
    "It should be noted that ∀i = j, p(edu i, edu j, r k) = 0, since no unit is self-dependent."
  ]
}